{"cursor":"3331","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Stephen Herbert Perrin', born January 22, 1946 and simply known as 'Steve Perrin', [http://rpggeek.com/rpgdesigner/13163/steve-\nperrin Steve Perrin biography resume on RPGGeek.com] is a game designer\nand technical writer/editor.\n\nPerrin is probably best known for creating the role-playing game [[RuneQuest]]\nfor Chaosium. While at Chaosium he also created [[Stormbringer (role-playing\ngame)|Stormbringer]], [[Worlds of Wonder (game)|Worlds of Wonder]],\n[[Elfquest]], and [[Superworld]], and contributed to [[Thieves World|Thieves'\nWorld]] and [[Call of Cthulhu (role-playing game)|Call of Cthulhu]]. One of his\nfirst contributions to the world of RPGs was \"The Perrin Conventions\", a set of\nhouse rules for [[Dungeons & Dragons]], which led to his work on\nRuneQuest. [http://www.maranci.net/rqpastold.htm The History of Runequest: A\nBright Beginning] 2001 (revised 13 July 2005); accessed 22 June 2008\n\nHe wrote the 1987 Champions role playing game supplement The Voice of Doom and\nthe Hero System rulebook \"Robot Warriors\".\n\nHe worked at Interplay Productions, Maxis, and Spectrum Holobyte, doing game\ndesign, playtesting, and writing manuals for such computer games as [[Star Trek:\nStarfleet Academy (video game)|Star Trek: Starfleet Academy]], [[SimCity 2000]],\nand [[Flight of the Intruder (video game)|Flight of the Intruder]] to name but a\nfew. He has also worked freelance for many of the major players in the games\nindustry including TSR, FASA, Hero Games, West End Games, and Iron Crown\nEnterprises.\n\n[[Steve Perrin's Quest Rules]] (SPQR) is the latest Steve Perrin role-playing\ngame, which he sells independently through Chaos Limited. In 2004 he\ncollaborated with Taldren on [[Black 9 Ops]] as a paper and pencil accompaniment\nto the company's Black9 PC and XBoxgame, which fell afoul of developer-publisher\nfriction and now looks to be unlikely to be published. Perrin decided to make\nBlack 9 Ops available for free.\n\nIn 2010 Perrin began creating PDF adventures for the games \"Icons\" and \"Mutants\nand Masterminds\". He has completed several scenarios for Vigilance Press and\nFainting Goat Press.\n\nPerrin earned a Bachelor of Arts in English from San Francisco State University.\n","linknr":131,"url":"Steve_Perrin","recorded":1375069092,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Steve_Perrin&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Steve_Perrin&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","#cite_note-1","/wiki/Game_designer","/wiki/Technical_writer","/wiki/Editing","/wiki/Role-playing_game","/wiki/RuneQuest","/wiki/Chaosium","/wiki/Stormbringer_(role-playing_game)","/wiki/Worlds_of_Wonder_(game)","/wiki/Elfquest","/wiki/Superworld","/wiki/Thieves_World","/wiki/Call_of_Cthulhu_(role-playing_game)","/wiki/Dungeons_%26_Dragons","#cite_note-2","/wiki/Interplay_Entertainment","/wiki/Maxis","/wiki/Spectrum_Holobyte","/wiki/Personal_computer_game","/wiki/Star_Trek:_Starfleet_Academy_(video_game)","/wiki/SimCity_2000","/wiki/Flight_of_the_Intruder_(video_game)","/wiki/TSR,_Inc.","/wiki/FASA_Corporation","/wiki/Hero_Games","/wiki/West_End_Games","/wiki/Iron_Crown_Enterprises","/wiki/Steve_Perrin%27s_Quest_Rules","